# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Board demo on managed BaaS — Supabase Cloud + Electric Cloud (board ADR-0008)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Copy to `board.cloud.env` (gitignored) and fill in YOUR project's values, then run
#  `bun run board:cloud:deploy`. The runbook (docs/runbooks/board-on-cloud.md) covers the one-time
#  manual steps this file assumes are done: create the Supabase project, create the Electric Cloud
#  source on its database, and authenticate the Supabase CLI.
#
#  Unlike the local stack (infra/compose/board.env), every value here is a REAL secret — never commit
#  `board.cloud.env`.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Supabase Cloud project ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project ref + the project's NEW API keys (Project Settings → API Keys). Cloud commands pass the ref
# explicitly and never depend on mutable `supabase link` state. BOARD_SUPABASE_URL is optional unless
# using a custom domain; the standard https://REF.supabase.co URL is derived from the ref.
BOARD_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=YOUR_REF
BOARD_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_REF.supabase.co
# Personal access token created while signed into the board demo's Supabase account. The cloud script
# passes it only to CLI subprocesses, independently of broken or unrelated global profile state.
BOARD_SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_YOUR_BOARD_ACCESS_TOKEN
BOARD_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx_xxxxxxxx
BOARD_SECRET_KEY=sb_secret_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx_xxxxxxxx

# ── Database connections (Project Settings → Database) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# DIRECT (port 5432): migrations + seed (DDL, BYPASSRLS as `postgres`). This is also the connection
# you give Electric Cloud when registering the source (it needs a logical-replication connection).
BOARD_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_DB_PASSWORD@db.YOUR_REF.supabase.co:5432/postgres
# TRANSACTION POOLER (Supavisor, port 6543): the edge functions' SUPABASE_DB_URL — serverless wants a
# pooled, transaction-mode connection (the functions already use postgres.js with prepare:false).
BOARD_DB_POOLER_URL=postgresql://postgres.YOUR_REF:YOUR_DB_PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres

# ── Regional invocation (STRONGLY recommended) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your project's region (the REGION token in the pooler host above, e.g. eu-central-1). The client
# sends it as the `x-region` header so edge functions execute NEXT TO THE DATABASE instead of next
# to the caller — without it, functions run near each visitor and every function→DB statement pays
# a cross-region round trip (measured: SG↔eu-central-1 ≈ 162ms/statement ⇒ ~3s per write).
BOARD_FUNCTIONS_REGION=REGION

# ── Electric Cloud (dashboard.electric-sql.cloud → your source) ──────────────────────────────────
# The Cloud shape endpoint with your source's id + secret. board-sync forwards to this verbatim; the
# secret stays server-side (set as a function secret), never reaching the browser.
# IMPORTANT: the board's membership-scoped shapes use a subquery `where`, a flagged Electric preview.
# On Electric Cloud it is activated per source by Electric staff on request — ask Electric to enable
# subqueries for your source, or self-host Electric with ELECTRIC_FEATURE_FLAGS and point this at it.
# Symptom if not activated: a member's shapes 400 {"where":["Subqueries are not supported"]}; admin works.
# See https://pgxsinkit.github.io/concepts/electric-subqueries/
ELECTRIC_SHAPE_URL=https://api.electric-sql.cloud/v1/shape?source_id=YOUR_SOURCE_ID&secret=YOUR_SOURCE_SECRET

# ── Frontend (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# `bun run board:cloud:dev` runs the local Vite client against this backend and DERIVES the browser
# vars from BOARD_SUPABASE_URL + BOARD_PUBLISHABLE_KEY above — you normally set nothing here. Override
# only if the browser should use a different origin/key than the deploy does:
# VITE_BOARD_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_BOARD_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx_xxxxxxxx

# ── CORS allow-list (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CORS allow-list for board-sync + board-write; `board:cloud:secrets` sets it as a function secret
# when present. Unset, the functions default to the e2e/preview origins (http://localhost:5173/5174)
# — NOT the dev-server port (5660), so set this for `board:cloud:dev`. Two forms:
#   `*`            — allow every origin by reflecting the request's Origin. Fine for a dev/demo
#                    backend: auth is a per-request bearer token (no cookies), so the origin list is
#                    hygiene, not the security boundary — and new dev ports never need a re-push.
#   exact origins  — comma-separated scheme+host[+port] (bare github.io origin, NOT the /demo path).
# Full hosted-demo setup (build variables, nightly reset, disabling signups): board ADR-0009 + the
# hosted-demo guide https://pgxsinkit.github.io/demo-and-harness/hosted-demo/
# BOARD_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*
# BOARD_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://YOUR_USER.github.io,http://localhost:5660
